<TEXT>
like an important head of 
state nelson mandela has been surrounded by dozens of beefy 
bodyguards in smart suits and sunglasses since he emerged from 
prison 
the african national congress has taken responsibility for 
mandelas safety publicly rejecting government offers of 
assistance anc activists have been mobilized to provide security 
for mandela despite short notice and little if any formal training 
when mandela addressed a wildly cheering crowd of about 120000 
people on his return tuesday to his home town of soweto he was 
guarded by about 30 big powerfullooking guards as mandela called 
for a new south africa the guards intently watched the crowd with 
binoculars for any threat 
the only sign of government security tuesday for mandela was a 
group of black municipal police on motorcycles who escorted his 
motorcade black green and gold anc flags fluttered on the police 
motorcycles 
it is an ironic turnabout for the man who until sunday was 
watched over by prison guards mandela was released after 27 years 
in some of south africas toughest jails for fighting the 
whiteminority government 
mandela faces serious threats both from white rightwing 
extremists and from rival black groups unhappy about his more 
moderate politics according to government security officials 
white extremists have been making threats against mandela for 
years and his safety is a major concern now that he is free said 
the officials who spoke on condition they not be identified 
some 2000 militants of the neonazi afrikaner resistance 
movement armed with guns whips and knives marched through 
pretoria saturday yelling hang mandela 
we are going to kill mandela and all his kind said one man 
brandishing a leather whip 
some leftwing black groups are reported to be unhappy with 
mandelas desire to end white rule peacefully through negotiation 
and south african intelligence has detected possible threats to his 
life the government officials said 
anc officials refuse to discuss arrangements for mandelas 
security saying that would compromise his safety they also 
declined to say where the phalanx of bodyguards came from and 
whether or not they are armed 
but security appears to be a major problem in the scenes of wild 
jubilation that greet mandela wherever he goes crowd control 
arrangements often break down and one person was killed and scores 
injured sunday in fighting in cape town as mandela made his first 
speech after leaving prison 
it has been a real nightmare said a marshall trying to 
control the crowd tuesday in soweto 
about 1000 marshals young men who belong to groups that 
support the anc controlled the crowd tuesday and also were 
involved in security marshals frisked people and searched vehicles 
coming into the stadium 
once marshal displayed a pistol and two knives he had taken from 
spectators 
mandela announced plans tuesday to visit colleagues in zambia 
and sweden as soon as possible there was no word on who will 
provide security when mandela leaves south africa 
</TEXT>
