<TEXT>
a woman who pleaded guilty to beating her 
22monthold son to death because of his constant crying received a 
life prison sentence and a stinging lecture from the judge 
perhaps the greatest blessing is that you will not be able to 
bear more children circuit judge lynn tepper told mary lee 
collins after her plea monday to a firstdegree murder charge in 
the death of her son joshua 
tepper said she reviewed photographs of joshuas emaciated and 
battered body and told ms collins she thought a jury would likely 
have recommended the death penalty had the case gone to trial 
ms collins will instead spend at least 25 years behind bars 
before becoming eligible for parole 
later in a jailhouse interview ms collins maintained she is 
not the babykiller she is made out to be 
i dont want people thinking of me as a monster that killed 
her son she said thats not who i am i love my kids i 
dont want anybody to think im saying oh i never hurt my kid 
i was mother teresa im not 
when she was arrested for killing joshua she already was on 
probation for abusing him his death put the state department of 
health and rehabilitative services under fire for sending joshua 
back to his mother less than a month before he died 
the case was the first of a series in which children died of 
abuse despite being under the supervision of agency caseworkers 
the cases include the muchpublicized pottytraining death of 
2yearold bradley mcgee of lakeland last july his parents face 
firstdegree murder charges 
joshua died from a massive head injury nov 25 1988 just hours 
after ms collins gave birth to a third boy 
the 22yearold zephyrhills woman told police she kicked joshua 
two days before he died 
she told police she had had enough of his constant crying 
ms collins also received 15 years for child abuse and five 
years for probation violation to be served at the same time 
</TEXT>
