<TEXT>
the past weeks dramatic moves by the united 
states the soviet union and their chief allies establish a 
framework for the most sweeping eastwest changes since world war 
ii 
the agreements open the way for the reunification of germany 
the reduction of superpower forces in europe and the expansion of 
ussoviet trade 
last week in the soviet union president mikhail s gorbachev 
won approval from the communist party central committee to give up 
the partys monopoly on power for the first time in about 70 years 
secretary of state james a baker iii who visited moscow last 
week made major progress with gorbachev toward an agreement for 
deep cuts in the superpowers longrange nuclear arsenals 
the swiftly moving talks culminated in ottawa on tuesday with 
the announcement of a framework for german unification agreed 
upon by the united states its major european allies the soviet 
union and east germany and a ussoviet agreement to limit their 
troops in central europe 
germany divided since the defeat of adolf hitler in 1945 still 
hosts more than a halfmillion foreign forces who have faced each 
other through the cold war 
this reunification agreement shows everybody has seen german 
unity will happen and they have agreed to a process that will 
provide stability and peace for europe said a west german 
diplomat in washington who asked not to be identified 
the german reunification agreement announced in ottawa sets up a 
twostep process to start after the march 18 elections in east 
germany 
moscow has insisted that germany remain neutral after 
reunification and the united states demands that germany remain 
part of the western alliance 
under the agreement the two germanys first would settle 
internal details then they would work with britain france the 
soviet union and united states the four main victorious allies in 
world war ii to establish agreements assuring peace and stability 
for europe 
such an approach is aimed at assuring the soviets and other 
europeans that germany seen as the source of the two world wars in 
this century would never again threaten its neighbors 
west german foreign minister hansdietrich genscher offered 
assurances of a reunited germanys peaceful intentions saying 
we tell all our neighbors what we want to unite the federal 
republic of germany the german democratic republic and the whole 
of berlin no less and no more we do not have territorial claims 
against any of our neighbors 
moves by leaders of east and west germany matched the pace of 
the other countries on tuesday west german chancellor helmut kohl 
and east german premier hans modrow agreed to begin talks next week 
to make the west german mark the official currency of east germany 
the ussoviet troop cuts announced by canadian external 
affairs minister joseph clark at the end of an eastwest meeting in 
ottawa would allow the united states and the soviet union to have 
195000 soldiers each on europes central front 
that would be a cut from 275000 for the united states and from 
565000 for the soviets and the united states would be allowed to 
have another 30000 troops elsewhere in europe 
us and soviet trade negotiators also said tuesday they expect 
to complete a treaty to normalize trade between the two nations in 
time for signing during the june summit meeting in washington 
the bush administration believes freer trade between the two 
nations would provide an important economic boost to gorbachevs 
political reforms 
during his eightday trip baker not only met with the soviets 
and nato allies but also visited czechoslovakia romania and 
bulgaria to encourage their moves toward democracy and freemarket 
economies 
however some eastwest issues still remain such as differences 
over regional conflicts in afghanistan where the united states 
supports guerrillas fighting the sovietbacked government and 
central america where the united states says the soviets have been 
supporting the nicaraguan government and guerrillas in el salvador 
</TEXT>
