<TEXT>
before the two germanys can merge as one 
nation they must overcome divisions that have grown out of 
radically different political and social systems and four decades 
of bitter rivalry 
here are some of the main issues the sides must resolve 
security the united states has insisted that a reunited 
germany remain in nato the soviet union has called for a neutral 
germany there is no decision yet whether a reunited germany would 
even have armed forces 
at present the soviet union has 380000 troops in east germany 
under the warsaw pact military alliance the united states france 
belgium britain and canada have more than 300000 soldiers in west 
germany under the nato alliance 
us and soviet forces in europe will be reduced under an 
agreement announced tuesday but the two german states also have 
formidible forces of their own nearly 400000 troops in the west 
german bundeswehr and about 200000 in the east german armed forces 
borders in the aftermath of world war ii germany lost 
considerable territory to poland and the soviet union these 
countries have insisted that the territorial changes have been 
formalized but there is considerable sentiment in both germanys to 
recover these lands at the bargaining table 
economy west germany with a population of 61 million is the 
largest country in the european economic community and the most 
powerful manufacturing nations in the trading group 
east germany with more than 16 million residents is a 
crucially important member of the moscowled comecon trading group 
but its economy once a model of central planning has been 
devastated in recent months by the exodus of tens of thousands of 
skilled workers to the west it has also polluted the environment 
under reunification west germany would probably bear the brunt 
of financial responsibility for east germany 
so far however the east german has rejected the west german 
proposal for a swift monetary union with the west german mark 
becoming the currency in the east instead east germany has 
appealed for 9 billion in bailout loans yet it has been unwilling 
to release basic economic data demanded by west germany as a 
condition for emergency aid 
government west germany is a parliamentary democracy with a 
stable and vibrant political system chancellor helmut kohl a 
christian democrat faces a challenge from the leftleaning social 
democrats in national elections dec 8 
east germany has been ruled by the communist party since its 
formation in 1948 out of the soviet occupation zone but its 
political system is now in great flux the partys power has badly 
eroded since the berlin wall was opened in november 
communist premier hans modrow faces the countrys first free 
elections on march 18 and the communists are expected to be 
defeated the new social democratic party of east germany is likely 
to emerge as the largest party but nearly a dozen other groups 
could win seats in parliament 
culture and outlook east germanys tightly controlled 
communist system and west germanys freewheeling capitalism have 
produced different character traits in many citizens east germans 
have come to expect zero unemployment from their socialist system 
if the two countries are unified there may be disillusionment in 
store for citizens on both sides 
