<TEXT>
the germany that was split into two after the may 1945 downfall 
of adolf hitlers third reich had been a unified nation for less 
than 75 years 
it was a loose confederation of principalities in the 17th 
century but under frederick ii 174086 prussia began emerging 
as a european power 
prussia and bavaria were expanded and many states were 
eliminated by the congress of vienna following napoleons defeat 
otto von bismarck a prussian was bent on fashioning a little 
germany one free from domination by the austrohungarian empire 
after victories in the austroprussian war of 1866 and the 
francoprussian war of 187071 william i was proclaimed the german 
emperor and germany became the chief european power 
europes old order came crashing down in world war i and 
germany the loser became the weak weimar republic in the 
turbulent years that followed the allied victory in november 1918 
hitler rose to power in 1933 and began his quest for world 
domination that led to the 193945 cataclysm of world war ii 
nazi germany surrendered unconditionally to the allied forces in 
may 1945 germany was divided into zones occupied by the four 
allied powers the region that is now east germany came under 
soviet control 
here is a look at major events that followed 
1946 the communist party becomes the ruling political force in 
east germany 
1949 the allied powers form the federal republic of germany 
or west germany the german democratic republic or east germany 
is officially founded as an independent state in the soviet zone of 
occupation 
1953 east germany puts down a workers uprising with the help 
of soviet tanks 
1961 faced with an exodus of highly skilled east german 
workers to the west east germany erects the berlin wall 
dissatisfaction in east germany persists in following years while 
west germany becomes an economic powerhouse 
augustseptember 1989 tens of thousands of east germans 
seeking passage to west germany pour into west german embassies in 
hungary poland and czechoslovakia thousands slip into austria 
through hungary 
october huge protests coincide with official commemorations of 
the 40th anniversary of communist rule in east germany and on oct 
18 egon krenz replaces hardline party chief erich honecker 
november the berlin wall opens 
december east german prime minister hans modrow urges closer 
ties with west germany and allows visafree travel between the 
germanys 
january modrow meets soviet president mikhail s gorbachev in 
moscow and says gorbachev is now more open to unification 
feb 1 modrow urges talks with west germany toward an eventual 
united fatherland independent of military blocs and governed by 
a joint parliament in berlin 
feb 2 west german foreign minister hansdietrich genscher 
says hes seeking support from the four world war ii allies the 
united states the soviet union britain and france for german 
unification kohl meets modrow the following day 
tuesday the allies and the two germanys agree on a process 
aimed at german reunification after the two germanys confer on 
settling legal political and economic issues all six foreign 
ministers will meet to discuss security issues 
