<TEXT>
mstislav rostropovich returned to the soviet 
concert stage after 16 years of exile leading his us orchestra 
in a rousing version of john philip sousas stars and stripes 
forever 
asked how he chose that bit of defiance rostropovich said 
later from my heart 
the late leonid brezhnev had banished rostropovich for refusing 
to renounce his principles and denounce his friend exiled author 
alexander solzhenitsyn but the cellist and conductor came back to 
a homeland where brezhnev and not he was discredited 
rostropovich returned as the worldrenowned director of the 
national symphony of the soviet unions rival superpower among 
those who attended the concert was president mikhail s gorbachevs 
wife raisa 
washingtons national symphony orchestra responded to 
rostropovichs emotional return with a brilliant performance in 
