at a time when dozens of prominent russians joined in a chorus 
of derision of the author rostropovich housed solzhenitsyn at his 
dacha for four years he sent a letter to four newspapers in 1970 
saying solzhenitsyn had suffered for speaking the truth all 
refused to publish it 
the presidium of the supreme soviet legislature restored the 
citizenship of rostropovich and his wife just a month ago and 
nullified the decree that stripped them of all their medals and 
honors 
rostropovichs fourconcert tour was arranged within days 
the new soviet minister of culture nikolai gubenko apologized 
in an article in the journal new times for the injustice of 
stripping the couple of citizenship the deplorable violation of 
human dignity should never be repeated he said 
