<TEXT>
the four world war ii allies vanquishers of nazi 
germany and occupiers of berlin have begun a process aimed at 
ensuring a unified germany will not pose a threat to world security 
foreign ministers from france britain the soviet union and 
united states announced tuesday that they would meet with their 
counterparts from east and west germany to discuss the alignment 
and military strength of a unified germany 
no date for such a meeting was given but before it takes place 
the two germanys will be left alone to tackle the considerable 
domestic hurdles that must be overcome before unity is possible 
with tuesdays announcement the powers that divided germany in 
1945 clearly acknowledged that reunification is inevitable now that 
communist rule has collapsed in east germany 
the brief oneparagraph statement did not address us concerns 
that a unified germany belongs to the nato alliance the soviet 
union seeks a neutral state the announcement said preliminary 
talks by lowerlevel officials on a unified germanys place in the 
new european order would begin shortly 
it was released about an hour before the soviet union and united 
states announced agreement on troops cuts in europe in which the 
soviets essentially accept a proposal by president bush and agree 
to a ceiling of 195000 troops for each side in central europe 
the agreement allows the united states to keep an additional 
30000 troops elsewhere in europe which mikhail s gorbachev had 
rejected just last week in seeking parity 
the announcements came during a conference of 23 nato and warsaw 
pact countries on opening up the worlds skies to surveillance by 
unarmed military planes on that issue they tentatively agreed to 
allow the first legal spy flights over each others territory the 
accord is to be finalized may 12 
officials have shied away from saying when a unified germany 
could become a reality but the two german states are moving 
swiftly toward that end on tuesday they set up a joint commission 
to set up a single currency 
at the white house spokesman marlin fitzwater said the 
president finds that a very reasonable approach to the unification 
question and we are quite supportive 
he called it a good beginning that ensures a certain degree of 
stability and sureness of course as we proceed through this 
west germanys foreign minister hansdietrich genscher said in 
ottawa on tuesday that he hoped a 35nation summit would address 
the issue of reunification in november 
the statemen on a single german state said sixcountry talks 
would focus on external aspects of the establishment of german 
unity including the issues of security of the neighboring states 
the foreign ministers made no comment after release of 
statement apparently reflecting their desire not to create undue 
expectations or prejudice the work facing the two germanys 
the fourpower plan adapted from a us initiative calls for 
the powers to address external security concerns only after east 
germans elect new leaders in free elections set for march 18 us 
officials said 
the plan was first set forward by secretary of state james a 
baker iii and dubbed two plus four for the two germanys and the 
allies 
the statement came after the foreign ministers met for several 
hours on the issue overshadowing the open skies conference 
the subject of german reunion has preoccupied nato and the 
warsaw pact since east germanys hardline communist leader erich 
honecker was ousted in november in a peaceful popular revolt 
the countrys discredited communists struggled to hold on to 
power but agreed last month to share power with opposition groups 
until the elections but there is no confidence in east germanys 
economy and the westward exodus has not abated 
genscher sought to reassure the world that a unified germany 
will not pose a threat to peace 
we tell all our neighbors what we want to unite the federal 
republic of germany the german democratic republic and the whole 
of berlin no less and no more we do not have territorial claims 
against any of our neighbors 
we seek a european germany not a german europe he said 
concern about germanys alignment stems from the strategic 
importance of the region and the possibility that a unified 
germany could again become an aggressor west germanys 
500000troop military is the biggest in western europe having 
been stoked by nato as a frontline defense against a warsaw pact 
invasion 
along with unification west german officials reportedly have 
promised to cut their forces by about 100000 troops and east 
germany would disband its army said david shorr an analyst at the 
british american security information council in washington 
the four powers were under pressure to keep the west german 
military in check and so they devised the two plus four plan 
said shorr who attended the conference 
nato has insisted that a unified germany be part of the 
16member north atlantic treaty organization 
but the soviet union which maintains about 380000 troops in 
east germany wants a unified germany demilitarized so it can be 
of no threat to others foreign ministry adviser vitaly churkin 
said monday 
britains foreign secretary douglas hurd said tuesday that few 
countries at the conference other than the soviet union have 
suggested a unified germany would be neutral 
genscher did not mention the neutrality issue specifically in 
his tuesday speech saying only that unification should occur in 
the context of integration of the european community and that 
nothing will be negotiated without participation of the four world 
war ii allies 
as part of the plan a unified germany also likely would 
renounce the use or stationing on its soil of nuclear weapons us 
officials said 
germanys neighbors in europe would have a voice in the talks 
during the second phase a polish embassy official said on 
condition he not be identified 
