hundreds of pushy barking sea lions some 
weighing more than 800 pounds are occupying at least 20 slips at 
the pricy pier 39 yacht basin delighting tourists but making life 
miserable for the marina and boat owners 
theyre cute as buttons but theyre very aggressive 
complained management spokeswoman lucy hobgoodbrown theyre not 
hurting business but theyre damaging the docks and they have bad 
breath 
the problem is that the herringgobbling sea lions are under the 
federal marine mammals protective act and may not be harassed 
hunted captured or killed 
i dont think you can even glare at them said marina 
manager sheila chandor 
national marine fisheries service biologist brad hanson said 
experts are mystified as to why the mammals have descended on such 
a public spot he said they usually prefer relatively isolated 
areas 
for more than a month the members of the herd with up to 300 
animals have been fishing frolicking and fighting at the boat 
berths which can sell for up to 50000 
pier 39 is a shopping restaurant and amusement complex just 
east of fishermans wharf 
the management is worried that the bulky animals adding 
unexpected tons of weight to floating docks will do serious damage 
to them and the attached water pipes and electric conduits when 
the whole gang is out of the water the docks are awash 
many electric meters at dock boxes have already been slapped 
loose when the sea lions haul out of the water the frisky 
creatures also scrape loose metal flashing and bash in relatively 
fragile dock boxes 
our guests wont leave chandor mourned but the 
tourists love it 
the piers main walkway runs directly in front of the sea lions 
adopted neighborhood during afternoons the place is a cacophony 
of barking blubber chattering tourists and clicking cameras 
the sea lions are all bulls most of them 3 to 5yearold 
juveniles hanson said some however are fullgrown and highly 
aggressive characters that have charged people venturing onto the 
docks no one has been hurt 
hanson thought the sea lions invaded the marina because the 
berths happened to be empty at the time boats are to be returned 
to the occupied docks next week and all hands are hoping for the 
best 
the mating season starts in may and were hoping the males 
here will go and join the ladies at the breeding grounds in the 
channel islands said hobgoodbrown the islands are north of los 
angeles near santa barbara 
