<TEXT>
an agreement giving the four allies of world war 
ii an advisory role in german reunification allayed fears in many 
countries about a military resurgence but some anxieties remained 
wednesday 
poland worried about its borders demanded a role in talks on 
the security aspects of unification 
prime minister margaret thatcher of britain who had not hidden 
her unease about a united germany felt much happier after the 
argreement tuesday in ottawa canada to hold the sixpower talks 
her aides said 
we were worried there wasnt a framework in which we and the 
russians and other interested parties could actually discuss the 
external side of this foreign secretary douglas hurd said now 
we have that framework we are much happier 
under the agreement the united states soviet union britain 
and france the allies that conquered nazi germany and still 
occupy berlin will confer with both germanys on the security 
ramifications of a single germany 
officials of east germany and west germany will negotiate after 
east german elections march 18 then join the allies to focus on 
the external aspects including the issues of security of the 
neighboring states the ottawa announcement said 
a sixpower agreement would be presented to a 35nation summit 
before the end of the year 
the soviet union whose casualties in world war ii were 
heaviest said wednesday its sensitivities should be taken into 
account 
we have a psychological trauma we lost 26 million people in 
the war foreign ministry spokesman gennady i gerasimov told a 
news briefing he added however that he believed europe was 
changing for the better 
premier tadeusz mazowiecki of poland said at the end of a 
threeday visit to britain we want to be present whenever the 
question of the security of germanys neighbors is discussed our 
stand is that our security matters cannot be settled by proxy for 
us we must be present 
mazowiecki said poland wants a treaty guaranteeing its borders 
which embrace territory populated by ethnic germans and annexed 
from germany at the end of world war ii no peace treaty was 
signed so poland has no formal guarantees 
west germany has said a unified germany would respect the border 
and make no territorial claims 
israeli officials referred to a statement monday by foreign 
minister moshe arens that the jewish state puts its faith in 
democracy 
no one but certainly us jews can think about reunification 
without somehow remembering what happened 50 years ago arens 
said referring to the 6 million jews killed by the nazis but he 
added if a united germany is a democratic germany then i 
dont think that there is a danger to be concerned about 
foreign minister hansdietrich genscher of west germany said 
after an hourlong meeting wednesday with mrs thatcher that final 
arrangements for reunification should be ready before the end of 
the year 
the prime minister has expressed firm support for german 
unity genscher told reporters outside mrs thatchers residence 
at 10 downing street it is an enormous encouragement for 
germans in east and west 
in november mrs thatcher said german unification was not on 
the agenda her aides say that was before east germany slid into 
economic chaos largely due to the mass flight of skilled workers 
to west germany 
the pace of events has surprised everyone hurd said 
wednesday 
mrs thatcher has been accused at home of wasting british 
influence by belatedly and grudgingly accepting german unification 
hurd said the most important issue for the sixpower talks was 
whether a single germany would remain in nato as the united states 
wants or becomes neutral as the soviet union prefers 
president francois mitterrand of france urged the 12nation 
european community which includes west germany to hasten its own 
moves toward closer union 
for me what is essential is that europe again take its true 
place in the world after the selfdestruction of two world wars 
he said in an interview with eight regional french newspapers 
the acceleration of the intergerman process should be 
accompanied by the acceleration of the european process 
ireland current president of the european community said it 
would summon the 12 nations soon to discuss german reunification 
