<TEXT>
the food and drug administration on wednesday 
approved a new drug that relieves the symptoms of endometriosis a 
disorder of the reproductive tract that affects more than 4 million 
us women 
the drug synarel is the first drug of its class to be approved 
for this condition it will be marketed by syntex corp 
synarel is administered as a nasal spray twice daily for six 
months and works by stimulating and then suppressing production of 
estrogen which controls the growth of the endometrial tissue that 
lines the uterus 
endometriosis occurs when this tissue which usually is shed 
monthly with menstruation migrates outside the uterus most often 
into the abdominal and pelvic region where it swells and bleeds 
during menstruation 
this tissue implants on the ovaries the intestines and the 
fallopian tubes where it can cause blockage and infertility 
symptoms of endometriosis include severe menstrual cramps pain 
during sexual intercourse painful urination and painful bowel 
movements 
side effects of synarel which is nafarelin acetate are the 
same as problems associated with menopause including hot flashes 
vaginal dryness and less commonly decreased sex drive syntex 
said a small loss of bone density also can occur but most is 
recovered after treatment is completed 
currently the most widely prescribed drug for treatment of the 
symptoms of endometriosis is danazol a derivative of a male sex 
hormone its side effects include weight gain decrease in breast 
size deepening of the voice acne oily skin and unwanted hair 
growth 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

