<TEXT>
a federal judge declared a mistrial in a 
chinese heroinsmuggling case wednesday after a key prosecution 
witness said he had lied under pressure and death threats from 
chinese officials 
us district judge william orrick halted proceedings in the 
case against three men accused in connection with 700000 worth 
of heroin found inside dead goldfish after the witness recanted 
his testimony and said he had been tortured in a shanghai prison 
he is seeking asylum in the united states 
the case which dates from march 1988 was the first 
international drug prosecution involving cooperation between 
chinese and us officials 
orrick said the breakdown of the trial was proof positive you 
cant meld the legal system in the peoples republic of china with 
the legal system in the united states 
assistant us attorney eric swenson told reporters orricks 
conclusion was valid for this case but im still confident that 
this type of problem does not have to affect future cases the 
legal system in china is almost identical to many of the western 
european systems 
