bitter northwest wind and heavy 
seas heaved gooey crude oil on shore wednesday forcing skimming 
boats to suspend operations while workers tackled the bulk of a 
coastal oil spill on the beach 
wind trailing a pacific winter storm gusted from 25 to 30 mph 
under a sunny sky while a mixture of tar balls brown foam and 
thick oil coated miles of the coast especially beaches exposed 
headon to the pounding surf 
in balboa about 10 miles south of here resident ralph gray said 
thick muck hit the beach for the first time wednesday 
i thought it was no big deal before since they said it was 
just a little amount of oil out there said gray 27 but we 
