<TEXT>
that famous gamin quality still shines in 
leslie carons face but an air of worldliness has been added to 
the star who entranced the film world as lili and gigi 
thats only natural since the french actressdancer at 58 has 
weathered 40 years in films she maintains an active career both 
as actress writer and she hopes as director but dont ask her 
to dance 
dancing oh no she declares it gets too hard 
the last time i was lured on the stage my swan song was the 
utmost i cant do anything to come close to that i dance seven 
minutes with baryshnikov and nureyev i am the only dancer ever to 
do that with both of them on a stage it was for a charity event at 
the met if you please 
after that i bowed out 
caron returned to hollywood for the launching of a new film 
courage mountain its an update of the heidi saga with 
juliette caton as the adolescent swiss heroine and charlie sheen as 
her army sweetheart caron plays the stern ironwilled 
headmistress of heidis boarding school in italy the school is 
caught in the turmoil of the start of world war i and the 
schoolgirls escape over the alps to safety pursued by a villainous 
italian 
ive been associated with childrens stories quite a lot in my 
career all those little girl parts observed the star i 
should think that was why they asked me to play in this film 
but lately i havent been playing such nice characters 
immediately after courage mountain i played a madam in a 
bordello and in the same year i played coco chanel a woman of 
tremendous authority 
this role was nice i felt like i was playing a schoolmarm who 
was a little bit crazy so intense about her teaching and the 
education of those children and the forming of their minds she was 
rather a dear lady i enjoyed playing that 
i saw her as a kind of pioneer i based her character a little 
bit on the bloomsbury set virginia woolf and all those women with 
high ideals i went much farther than the part demanded but this 
is what i had in mind 
leslie caron became an immediate star in 1951 when gene kelly 
picked her out of roland petits paris ballet to dance with him in 
an american in paris she was barely 16 the daughter of a 
french chemist and an american dancer she followed with such films 
as lili the glass slipper daddy long legs with fred 
astaire the oscarwinning gigi fanny father goose 
with cary grant and promise her anything 
what does she remember fondly of her hollywood years 
gene kellys house on saturday night it was open house there 
were no keys on the locks in those days from eight oclock on 
anyone who felt the need for a good drink and good company would 
wander in guests would sit down at the piano or start singing or 
start dancing or just talk 
there were so many entertainers there on saturday night that 
it was really quite thrilling and always producerdirector 
stanley donen would be sleeping through it all 
what does she remember not so fondly 
the iron rule of the studio mgm was uncomfortable she 
recalled one was a property of the studio it was a little 
regimented you had to do what they told you im very selfwilled 
as you may have noticed i didnt always want to do the films that 
the studio wanted me to do so i would stand up to them sometimes 
that was frightening it took some courage 
why did i leave i just liked liberty i didnt want to be 
under contract i tried to leave from the moment i was locked in 
there it took me eight years to get my liberty back which was 
probably a foolish thing on my part because i think the studio 
system was good especially for actresses you had constant work 
had i been a little more intelligent and been able to work with the 
system i could have found some parts i could have worked instead 
of being rebellious as i was 
with the lshaped room in 1962 she proved she was a 
dramatic actress as well as a dancer her three marriages to 
meatpacking heir george hormel british director peter hall and 
american director michael laughlin ended in divorce 
with her two children by hall on their own she has engaged in a 
wide range of activities from serving on film festival juries to 
writing short stories and next directing 
ive been writing a script and i want to direct it she 
said its my third script and i want to direct this one id 
love to start on that profession dont tell me its a bit late i 
dont believe it 
its an experience actors want to have gone through i think 
every actor always has wanted to do that usually they stop after 
one experience charlie laughton directed one film so did albert 
finney also frank sinatra kirk douglas jack lemmon marlon 
brando 
for the past 13 years caron has maintained her home in paris 
sometimes i think its too nice there she said sometimes 
you can just be lulled away by the wonderful wonderful things that 
happen in paris premieres theater films dinners friends you 
could just waste your life away doing pleasant things not working 
im a hardworking person i love to work 
</TEXT>
