company will withdraw its mineral water from worldwide distribution 
because small amounts of a naturally occurring toxic gas passed 
through a dirty filter and contaminated some bottles 
gustave leven told a news conference the company took the step 
because half measures were not possible 
traces of benzene have been found in samples of the water in the 
united states canada the netherlands and denmark in recent days 
but only part of the production will be withdrawn from the 
french market after a preliminary ruling by the health ministry 
that it poses no danger to the public leven said 
