million bottles of perrier were withdrawn from the us market 
after benzene was detected there 
benzene a chemical used in cleaning solvents entered the water 
in trace amounts when workers failed to change a pipe filter at 
perriers natural spring at vergeze in southern france 
the water and the natural carbon dioxide gas that makes it 
bubbly are normally separated underground then carried up separate 
pipes to the bottling plant perrier managing director frederik 
zimmer said 
a filter on the gas pipe that removes benzene and other 
impurities had not been changed in several months zimmer said 
malfunctioning and allowing naturallyoccuring benzene to seep 
through 
we dont know exactly how long the filter had been there 
thats the problem said zimmer it was complete negligence 
