the european commission decided 
wednesday to oppose air frances purchase of a controlling interest 
in union de transports aeriens a privately held french airline 
the commission found that stateowned air frances acquisition 
violates competition rules of the european economic community a 
commission spokesman said 
the spokesman who declined to be identified by name said the 
commission plans to send a formal statement of objection to air 
france and the french government he said the letter would open the 
way for discussions on what actions need to be taken to eliminate 
the commissions objections 
eec officials say air france could be forced to shed some of the 
routes it acquired through its uta purchase 
air frances purchase values uta frances biggest private 
airline at almost 7 billion francs or around 12 billion on 
jan 17 air france paid 38 billion francs for a 546 percent 
stake in uta 
air france bought the uta stake from chargeurs sa a holding 
company with transportation and textile interests chargeurs had 
controlled 829 percent of utas capital 
air france and uta officials were unavailable for comment 
wednesday 
