<TEXT>
business failures fell to the lowest level in 
more than a decade last year as massive savings and loans flops 
and the real estate slump subsided dun amp bradstreet corp reported 
wednesday 
business failures nationwide declined 129 percent to 49719 
from 57099 in 1988 said dun amp bradstreet a new yorkbased 
marketer of business information 
the decline was most pronounced in texas where business 
failures dropped 324 percent to 5323 however failures rose 419 
percent in massachusetts to 789 as new england states reported an 
increase in bankruptcies 
business failures according to the report are defined as 
companies that cease operations for a number of reasons including 
bankruptcy foreclosure or reorganization 
fewer failures were reported in agriculture mining 
manufacturing and the services sector as well as in wholesale and 
retail trade 
but the finance insurance and real estate sectors registered a 
91 percent increase in business failures to 2770 from 2540 in 
1988 the report said 
the troubled savings and loan industry and the subsequent 
stress in the real estate sector drove failures up earlier this 
year but the upward trend appears to be subsiding said joseph 
w duncan a dun and bradstreet economist 
