san franciscobased transamerica credited strong performances in 
its insurance and finance businesses for its robust gain in 
fourthquarter profit 
for the three months ended dec 31 the company posted net 
income of 761 million or 95 cents a share up 31 percent from 
58 million or 73 cents a share in the same period in 1988 
the 1988 fourthquarter results included 15 million in gains 
from investments 
for all of 1989 transamericas net income was 3322 million 
or 418 a share up from 2621 million or 330 a share in 
1988 the annual figures include capital gains of 402 million in 
1989 and 108 million in 1988 
the 1988 results also include a 369 million onetime reduction 
in the first quarter because of a new rule on accounting for income 
taxes 
