<TEXT>
the chicago mercantile exchange on wednesday 
unveiled a blueprint for the 1990s that foresees eastern european 
participation in the mercs agricultural markets and new sources of 
revenue for exchange members 
but the first objective of the worlds secondlargest commodity 
futures exchange is to regain public confidence after last years 
bruising revelation of a federal tradingfraud investigation the 
mercs board of governors said in a statement 
in order to maintain our successful momentum there must be 
absolute confidence in the integrity of our markets the 
statement said 
the continuing investigation of trading practices at the merc 
and the larger chicago board of trade has yielded indictments 
against 48 people 26 of them merc traders 
leo melamed chairman of the merc boards executive committee 
said the freemarket revolution in eastern europe promises to 
revitalize the mercs agricultural futures and options markets 
which were overshadowed by the wildly successful development of 
financial futures in the 1980s 
people in the emerging democracies of eastern europe want more 
meat and importers there can be taught how to protect their 
businesses from market fluctuations by using futures and options to 
lock in prices in advance melamed said in a telephone interview 
in addition to its existing cattle hog and porkbelly 
contracts the merc may develop new hedging instruments 
specifically for the eastern european market he said 
were going to make that into quite a priority because it 
looks like theres a demand for it melamed said 
the board also proposed a new business venture the cme resource 
and service co to develop products and services for market users 
and divide the profits among the mercs approximately 2700 members 
some of the ventures cme resource may pursue include publishing 
telecommunications services accounting services and tradeclearing 
for markets other than the merc melamed said 
the venture would be modeled after globex an automated global 
trading network the merc is developing with reuters holdings plc 
that will return profits to exchange members 
globex will be launched in the spring the merc said 
</TEXT>
